The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Friday, March 11, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Purulia, March 10: Four cops were injured in a pitched battle with about 200 villagers trying to free a person arrested late last night on charges of highway robbery.

 A team of 50 officials had gone to Damodarpur in Purulia district, 250 km from Calcutta, to arrest Gunadhar Shabar, who was wanted for several highway dacoities in Puncha and Hura areas of the district. The squad, led by additional superintendent of police Tapasranjan Ghosh, was attacked with stones and arrows while returning with Gunadhar in custody.

 Barasat: Ayesha Khatun, a Class VIII student of Dhanyakuria High Madarsa in North 24-Parganas, about 30 km from Calcutta, died while giving her senior Madarsa examination. K. Adhikary, the chief medical officer of health of North 24-Parganas, said Ayesha started bleeding from the nose and ears in the examination hall and was rushed to a local hospital where she was declared dead.

